President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of New Mexico due to severe storms and flooding that occurred between July 23-28, 2013. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding is available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Nancy M. Casper has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations. Additional designations may be made if requested by the state and further damage assessments warrant it.